<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORDECAI GORELIK; SET DESIGNER, PLAYWRIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mordecai Gorelik, 90, a theatrical set designer who also wrote, produced and 
directed plays. 
</P>
<P>
Known primarily for his scenic designs for such productions as "Golden Boy," 
"Tortilla Flat," "All My Sons," "A Hatful of Rain," Gorelik, also translated 
and adapted Swiss playwright's Max Frisch's "The Firebugs" in a widely heralded 
off-Broadway production. He taught at Southern Illinois University and Cal 
State San Jose and two years ago published "Toward a Larger Theater," a book of 
seven of his plays. In Sarasota, Fla., on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
