<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUCHANAN ON COLLABORATORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So Buchanan is calling the collaborators to account? It seems to me that a 
world struggling to free itself from opportunistic and uncaring overlords is 
bound to spawn leaders like Lenin, Mao, Castro, Ho and Ortega, standard-bearers 
dreaming of national self-determination, affordable education and health care 
and guaranteed employment. It's ironic that when the political offspring of 
such revolutionaries begin to live like fat-cat Republicans, forcing the people 
to throw them out, Buchanan should be the one sounding the call for a domestic 
blood bath. 
</P>
<P>
I ask him to look at how two terms of Reagan Administration mismanagement have 
devastated our nation's economic, educational and health-care systems. We'll be 
decades putting this country back together, spending billions to bailout banks, 
savings and loans, pension funds and insurance companies. The United States may 
never again be a world leader in public education and health care. We've been 
raped by petty opportunists and uncaring ideologues, and indeed the time has 
come to call the collaborators to account. Step forward please, Mr. Buchanan. 
</P>
<P>
JON WILLIAMS 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 
</P>
