<HEADLINE>
<P>
DR. NEIL SOLOMON: FAT SUBSTITUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: For some time, I've been thinking of going on a diet because I know I 
should lose about 40 pounds. But I've heard about a new product that is 
supposed to look like fat and to taste like fat, but which doesn't have any 
calories. 
</P>
<P>
I think something such as this would make dieting much easier, and I'd like to 
know if you have any idea when it will be available. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: One of the nation's leading food producers is working on a product 
called Olestra, which, as you say, is supposed to look and taste like fat but 
is calorie-free. The product's technical name is sucrose polyester. 
</P>
<P>
Although Olestra has been under development for several years, it will probably 
take several more years before it reaches the market. There are always 
rationalizations to delay going on a diet, but the best time is always now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
