<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA ON CBS, BUT IT MAY NOT BE LIVE IN L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Loyola Marymount's first-round NCAA tournament game against New Mexico State at 
8:30 Friday night at Long Beach will be nationally televised by CBS. 
</P>
<P>
The East Coast will get it live at 11:30 p.m., the West Coast delayed at the 
same time. 
</P>
<P>
Channel 2, however, could decide to show it live, and a decision is expected to 
be made today. 
</P>
<P>
Showing the game live would mean preempting a Bugs Bunny special, "Dallas," and 
possibly "Falcon Crest." Or the station might push back "Falcon Crest" from 10 
to around 10:30 p.m., and along with it the 11 o'clock news to 11:30 or so. 
</P>
<P>
The CBS game Thursday night will be Ohio State vs. Providence. Channel 2 will 
show it delayed at 11:30 p.m. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
