<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tommy Houston overtook Elton Sawyer on a restart with 16 laps remaining and won 
the 200-lap NASCAR Busch Grand National stock car race at Martinsville (Va.) 
Speedway. It was the 20th victory of Houston's Grand National career, but just 
the first in a 200-lap event at Martinsville's .526-mile, low-banked oval for 
the veteran driver from Hickory, N. C. 
</P>
<P>
Houston, who averaged 64.212 m.p.h. in a Buick, won $13,395. 
</P>
