</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roy Tarpley, Dallas Maverick forward, was fined $250 after missing the team's 9 
a.m. flight to Houston Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Tarpley said his home in North Dallas suffered a power outage early Saturday, 
causing his alarm clock to stop. 
</P>
<P>
If Tarpley misses another team flight, practice or game before Saturday, he 
would be in violation of the league's anti-drug guidelines set for two-time 
offenders and would have to undergo a drug test. 
</P>
