<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kristina Lindgren and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRACING: School officials know "drug babies" are coming soon (B1), but they're 
wary because there is no track record for them. . . . "We're at a loss as to 
how to (work) with these kids because we don't have any here yet," says an 
official for the Newport-Mesa district. "We're equipped to handle disadvantaged 
and disabled students. . . . What we don't (know) is what the numbers would be 
and if there's some specialty we need to know." Kristina Lindgren and Mark I. 
Pinsky 
</P>
</TEXT>
