<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EL SALVADOR; 
</P>
<P>
SLAIN ARCHBISHOP PROPOSED AS SAINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Salvadoran Roman Catholic Church will ask the Vatican to declare the late 
Archbishop Oscar Arnulfo Romero a saint. Romero was gunned down in 1980 as he 
conducted a Mass in San Salvador. Auxiliary Archbishop Gregorio Rosa Chavez 
said the church will begin the process of canonization to mark the 10th 
anniversary of Romero's murder on March 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
