<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LEBANON; 
</P>
<P>
CAR BOMB HURTS 20 AT W. BEIRUT MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A car bomb exploded in a marketplace a few yards from a Syrian army checkpoint 
in Muslim West Beirut, wounding 20 people, police said. The blast in the 
crowded Barbir marketplace sent shrapnel flying and ripped through a nearby 
sandbagged Syrian position. The explosion came amid renewed inter-Christian 
fighting in the eastern sector of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
