ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
FORUM PLANNED FOR COUNCIL CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A forum for City Council candidates is scheduled for Wednesday at 7 p.m. in the 
council chambers at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
All eight candidates running for two council seats have agreed to attend the 
event, which may be the last candidates' forum before the March 27 election, 
according to Marilyn DeWitt of the League of Women Voters. The league is 
sponsoring the forum. 
</P>
<P>
Galen F. Ambrose, 49, Gwen Forsythe, 35, and Dennis K. Pollman, 44, are running 
for the District 3 seat, which covers the neighborhood known as The Hill. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Antos, 44, James Cook, 37, Marilyn Bruce Hastings, 61, Douglas Hoxing, 
35, and Joe Rullo, 54, are running in District 1, which includes the downtown 
area and Surfside. 
</P>
