<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES LAUNCHES DAILY EDITION IN VENTURA COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times today begins publication of a daily Ventura County Edition. 
</P>
<P>
Local news and advertising will appear in Part B seven days a week. 
</P>
<P>
A new weekly section called Ventura County Life will debut on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"Our primary goal is to provide the most complete source of daily countywide 
news coverage available anywhere," said Jeffrey S. Hall, president of The 
Times' Valley and Ventura County Editions. 
</P>
<P>
The edition will be produced by a staff of reporters, photographers and editors 
in Ventura and printed at the Times Valley plant in Chatsworth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES; NEWSPAPERS -- VENTURA COUNTY; SCHEDULES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031290-0106 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 188541 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 12, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
