<P>
AFTERSHOCKS JOLT 2-COUNTY AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two mild aftershocks to the Upland earthquake shook parts of Los Angeles and 
San Bernardino counties early today, but no injuries or damage were reported, 
seismologists said. 
</P>
<P>
The first aftershock at 3:26 a.m. measured 3.3 on the Richter scale, and the 
second, at 3:29 a.m., measured 2.8, said Robert Finn of the California 
Institute of Technology in Pasadena. Both were centered four miles northwest of 
Upland. 
</P>
