3 DIE, DOZENS HURT IN FOG CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GREEN BAY, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fiery, chain-reaction collision of 45 vehicles on a fog-shrouded, interstate 
bridge killed at least three people and hospitalized two dozen others early 
today, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"The catalyst was a three-car accident. How that happened I don't know," said 
Deputy Chief of Traffic Robert Kreuser. "From there it was a chain-reaction. It 
just piled up." 
</P>
<P>
The crash killed at least three people, said police Capt. Larry Gille, who was 
coordinating rescue efforts in the northbound lanes of the Tower Drive Bridge 
on Interstate 43, which spans the Fox River. 
</P>
<P>
At least 24 people were treated at the city's two hospital emergency rooms and 
three were admitted, officials said. 
</P>
